{"title_page": "Geranium dalmaticum", "text_new": "{{speciesbox\n|image = Geranium dalmaticum.jpg\n|genus = Geranium\n|species = dalmaticum\n|authority = (Beck) [[Rech.f.]]\n}}\n\n'''''Geranium dalmaticum''''', commonly called '''Dalmatian cranesbill''', is a [[species]] of [[hardiness (plants)|hardy]] flowering [[herbaceous plant|herbaceous]] [[perennial plant]] in the [[genus]] ''Geranium'' of the [[family (biology)|family]] Geraniaceae.<ref>https://www.uniprot.org/taxonomy/387082</ref> It is [[native plant|native]] to [[Dalmatia]] on the west coast of Croatia. Growing to only {{convert| 10|cm|in|abbr=on}} tall by up to {{convert|50 |cm|in|abbr=on}} broad, it is cultivated as a garden subject in [[temperateness|temperate]] regions for its low mound of aromatic leaves and soft mauve colored flowers.<ref name=Phillips1993>{{Citation | last1 = Phillips | first1 = Ellen | last2 = Colston Burrell | first2 = C. | year = 1993 | title = Rodale's illustrated encyclopedia of perennials | pages = 373\u201376 | isbn = 0-87596-570-9 | publisher = Rodale Press| location = Emmaus, Pa.}}</ref> The palmately lobed glossy green leaves are tinted red in the Autumn.<ref>{{cite book|title=RHS A-Z encyclopedia of garden plants|year=2008|publisher=Dorling Kindersley|location=United Kingdom|isbn=1405332964|pages=1136}}</ref> It has gained the [[Royal Horticultural Society]]'s [[Award of Garden Merit]].<ref>{{cite web|title=''Geranium dalmaticum'' AGM|url=http://apps.rhs.org.uk/plantselector/plant?plantid=859|work=RHS Plant Finder|publisher=Royal Horticultural Society|accessdate=27 July 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web  | url= https://www.rhs.org.uk/plants/pdfs/agm-lists/agm-ornamentals.pdf | title = AGM Plants - Ornamental | date = July 2017 | page = 43 | publisher = Royal Horticultural Society | accessdate = 2 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category|Geranium dalmaticum}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q3513733}}\n\n[[Category:Geranium|dalmaticum]]\n[[Category:Flora of Croatia]]\n\n\n{{Geraniaceae-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{speciesbox\n|image = Geranium dalmaticum.jpg\n|genus = Geranium\n|species = dalmaticum\n|authority = (Beck) [[Rech.f.]]\n}}\n\n'''''Geranium dalmaticum''''', commonly called '''Dalmatian cranesbill''', is a [[species]] of [[hardiness (plants)|hardy]] flowering [[herbaceous plant|herbaceous]] [[perennial plant]] in the [[genus]] ''Geranium'' in the Geraniaceae [[family (biology)|family]].<ref>https://www.uniprot.org/taxonomy/387082</ref> It is [[native plant|native]] to [[Dalmatia]] on the west coast of Croatia. Growing to only {{convert| 10|cm|in|abbr=on}} tall by up to {{convert|50 |cm|in|abbr=on}} broad, it is cultivated as a garden subject in [[temperateness|temperate]] regions for its low mound of aromatic leaves and soft mauve colored flowers.<ref name=Phillips1993>{{Citation | last1 = Phillips | first1 = Ellen | last2 = Colston Burrell | first2 = C. | year = 1993 | title = Rodale's illustrated encyclopedia of perennials | pages = 373\u201376 | isbn = 0-87596-570-9 | publisher = Rodale Press| location = Emmaus, Pa.}}</ref> The palmately lobed glossy green leaves are tinted red in the Autumn.<ref>{{cite book|title=RHS A-Z encyclopedia of garden plants|year=2008|publisher=Dorling Kindersley|location=United Kingdom|isbn=1405332964|pages=1136}}</ref> It has gained the [[Royal Horticultural Society]]'s [[Award of Garden Merit]].<ref>{{cite web|title=''Geranium dalmaticum'' AGM|url=http://apps.rhs.org.uk/plantselector/plant?plantid=859|work=RHS Plant Finder|publisher=Royal Horticultural Society|accessdate=27 July 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web  | url= https://www.rhs.org.uk/plants/pdfs/agm-lists/agm-ornamentals.pdf | title = AGM Plants - Ornamental | date = July 2017 | page = 43 | publisher = Royal Horticultural Society | accessdate = 2 March 2018}}</ref> \n\n==References==\n{{Commons category|Geranium dalmaticum}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q3513733}}\n\n[[Category:Geranium|dalmaticum]]\n[[Category:Flora of Croatia